        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <h2>How does Plantah Work?</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-offset-1">
            <p>Simply find a plant that you would like to begin with on the home
            page, and start planning. By clicking the plant's button, you will be
            brought to the plant's individual page where you can see all of its relevant
            information. Get an idea about to plant near it by viewing its 'friends'
            and 'foes.'</p>
            <p>Plantah was built with Ruby on Rails. Individuals plants exist
            in a Plants table, storing all the information that you need to know
            to get the plant in the ground and growing. Plants are associated with
            other plants in order to model the companion vs antagonist (friend and foe)
            relationship that many plants have.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

